Package nl.sense_os.service

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ISenseServiceCallback  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AliveChecker
    This class is responsible for checking if the SenseService is still alive when it should be.
    BootRx
    This class is responsible for automatically starting the Sense service when the phone boots up.
    BuildConfig  
    DataTransmitter
    This class is responsible for initiating the transmission of buffered data.
    ISenseServiceCallback.Stub
    Local-side IPC implementation stub class.
    MsgHandler
    This class is responsible for handling the sensor data that has been collected by the different sensors.
    NetworkMonitor
    This class is responsible for monitoring the connectivity status of the phone, and restarts the Sense service when connectivity is regained after it was lost.
    NetworkReceiver  
    R  
    R.attr  
    R.drawable  
    R.string  
    R.xml  
    SenseService
    Main Sense service class.

    Activities can bind to this service and call functions to: log in; register; start sensing; start/stop individual sensor modules; set and get properties; When the #toggleMain(boolean) method is called to start the sensing, the service starts itself and registers itself as a foreground service so it does not get easily killed by Android.
    SenseServiceStub
    Implementation of the service's AIDL interface.
    ServiceStateHelper
    This class is responsible for keeping track of the Sense service state and updating the status bar notification when the service is started or changes login status.
